      <abstract label="Abstract">Papers of an author, editor for <title render="italic" linktype="simple">The Reporter, </title>and special assistant to President Lyndon B. Johnson. The collection consists of drafts, correspondence, and research and indexing material for two books, <title render="italic" linktype="simple">The Fourth Branch of Government </title>(1959), which was a study of government and the press, and <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Power in Washington: A Critical Look at Today's Struggle to Govern in the Nation's Capital </title>(1964), an examination of the executive and legislative branches.</abstract>
